                        <support>
                           <p>Two <material key="plumbum">lead</material> (<seg cert="low">or <material key="aes">bronze</material>
                              </seg>) <objectType>tablet</objectType>s each shaped rather like a shoe-heel (i. <width unit="metre">0.055</width> × <height unit="metre">0.057</height> × <depth unit="metre">0.0027</depth>; ii. <width unit="metre">0.055</width> × <height unit="metre">0.056</height> × <depth unit="metre">0.0023</depth>); probably a single piece of metal folded in half and later broken along this weakened line.</p>
                        </support>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout> Each <rs type="execution" ref="scalpro">scratched</rs> on one face, on the surface that would have been concealed by the fold.</layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote> i. <height unit="metre">0.007–0.01</height>; ii. <height unit="metre">0.005-0.007</height>; in ii. <foreign xml:lang="grc">Α</foreign> has [[crooked]] cross-bar; <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ν</foreign> written backwards; <foreign xml:lang="grc">Θ</foreign>  is diamond-shaped, which perhaps suggests second to third centuries A.D., but the lettering is too informal for confidence. Looks Roman rather than Hellenistic.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
               </physDesc>
